'''Tiberius Ogden''' was an elder member of the [[Wizengamot]] who resigned in protest due to [[Cornelius Fudge]]'s appointment of [[Dolores Umbridge]] as [[Hogwarts High Inquisitor|High Inquisitor]] at [[Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry]] and the continuing [[Campaign to discredit Albus Dumbledore and Harry Potter|campaign]] by the [[British Ministry of Magic|Ministry of Magic]] and the [[Daily Prophet]] to discredit [[Albus Dumbledore]] and [[Harry Potter]].<ref name="OOTP15">{{OOTP|B|15}}</ref>

Tiberius Ogden was the friend who told Professor [[Tofty]], [[Harry Potter]]'s [[Defence Against the Dark Arts]] [[Ordinary Wizarding Level|O.W.L.]] Examiner, that he could perform a corporeal [[Patronus Charm|Patronus]].<ref name="OOTP31">{{OOTP|B|31}}</ref>

==Etymology==
The name "Tiberius" is a Roman praenomen, or given name, meaning "of the Tiber" in Latin. The Tiber is the river that runs through Rome. {{w|Tiberius}} was the second Roman emperor, the stepson of emperor {{w|Augustus}}.

==Behind the scenes==
*Tiberius Ogden may have been the same person as [[Cormac McLaggen]]'s uncle [[Tiberius]], as mentioned by [[Horace Slughorn]] in {{HBP}}.
*He may have been related to [[Bob Ogden]], who also worked for the Ministry of Magic as the Head of the [[Magical Law Enforcement Patrol]], or the makers of [[Ogden's Old Firewhiskey]].

